1. Moduled act as a library in C would act you can create variables or functions and use them in whatever file imports the module. If you 
want to use modules, you will need to use webpack.

2. utilities.js

export const square = (a) => a*a +3;

export const name = (name) => name;

3. index.js

import {square, name} from './utilities';
console.log(square(2));

console.log(name('Russ Butt'));
